---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const divider = `<svg class="spectrum" width="120" height="18" viewBox="0 0 120 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <path d="M0 9 H30 Q34 9 36 4 T42 9 H62 Q66 9 68 13 T74 9 H88 Q91 9 92 6 T96 9 H120"
        stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" />
</svg>`;
---

<Base>
  <p class="kicker">Chemistry · Applied Mathematics · University of Washington</p>

  <div class="intro">
    <div class="intro-text">
      <h1>Hello!</h1>
      <p>
        I'm an undergraduate at the University of Washington studying chemistry and
        applied mathematics, and I do research in an experimental physical chemistry
        lab. This site is my home base! It's all about research, course notes, and the occasional
        piece of writing.
      </p>
    </div>
    <img
      class="portrait"
      src="/portrait.jpg"
      alt="Conor Frizelle in graduation regalia at Suzzallo Library"
      width="900"
      height="1350"
    />
  </div>

  <p>
    Beyond research and being a student, I am also trying to learn how to be the best educator I
    can be. My dream is to be a professor myself, so I have a youtube channel where I talk/teach about
    things that interest me. Check it out at the bottom of this page!
  </p>

  <Fragment set:html={divider} />

  <h2>Currently</h2>
  <p>
    Working on terahertz single-pixel imaging with compressive sensing, and a
    paper on phthalate composition in storm drain markers (in review).
  </p>
  <p>
    I am also running a home lab, currently trying to turn ethyl acetate into
    ethanol and sodium acetate.
  </p>
</Base>